  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency response for the people affected by conflict in Mukohwa and Loashi Masisi territory</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project aims to support the most vulnerable people who largely have settled unsheltered in public places, who are in need of non-food items (NFI) . This includes those with special needs (older people, pregnant and lactating women, unaccompanied children, those with disabilities and chronic diseases) who are unsheltered. An unconditional cash intervention is appropriate in the affected area to cover the needs for non-food items  and health especially for the disabled persons living with chronic diseases. HelpAge DRC and CAFOD will select the beneficiary households  in collaboration with the  IDPs local committee, the beneficiaries representation, the representative of the humanitarian affairs division, local authorities and members of Local Participatory Governance Committees (CLGP) based on criteria of vulnerability proposed above and which will be validated by all stakeholders.</narrative>
  </description>
